Prerequisites
The following are prerequisites for the successful completion of this procedure:

Outlook client is installed.

Permissions to the DDDATABASE mailbox have been granted.

Actions
Navigate to the Control Panel on the workstation.

Access the Mail control panel applet.

Click on Show Profiles

Make sure "Prompt for a profile..." is selected

Click on Add

Type "DDDATABASE" as the name of the profile and click OK

Select Manually configure..." and click Next

Select "Microsoft Exchange..." and click Next

Enter "exchange.brisbane.qld.gov.au" as the Server and dddatabase@brisbane.qld.gov.au as the User Name and click Check Name

Click Next

Click Finish

To access the DDDATABASE mailbox restart Outlook and when prompted for the profile to use select DDDATABASE
